1
00:01:12,000 --> 00:01:15,060
There was nothing special
about Somerset County.

2
00:01:15,337 --> 00:01:17,771
It was a deeply ordinary place.

3
00:01:18,740 --> 00:01:21,106
No astonishing thing
ever happened there.

4
00:01:22,244 --> 00:01:25,145
The people who lived there
were just regular people.

5
00:01:25,747 --> 00:01:29,410
And the animals...
Well, they were just plain old animals.

6
00:01:30,852 --> 00:01:33,286
They didn't question the order of things.

7
00:01:35,323 --> 00:01:38,156
So, the days passed,
one very much like the other.

8
00:01:39,995 --> 00:01:43,624
But, one spring, on a small farm,

9
00:01:44,433 --> 00:01:46,560
a little girl did something,

10
00:01:47,102 --> 00:01:50,970
something that
would change everything.

11
00:03:29,070 --> 00:03:30,503
What are you doing?

12
00:03:34,843 --> 00:03:36,276
Fern, go back to bed.

13
00:03:36,378 --> 00:03:38,346
You're not going to kill it, are you?

14
00:03:38,446 --> 00:03:40,471
It's a runt. Now, go back to bed.

15
00:03:41,516 --> 00:03:44,314
No, it's not fair!
It can't help being born small.

16
00:03:44,419 --> 00:03:45,386
Careful.

17
00:03:45,620 --> 00:03:48,384
If I'd been born small,
would you have killed me?

18
00:03:48,623 --> 00:03:49,817
Of course not.

19
00:03:50,825 --> 00:03:54,761
A little girl is one thing.
A runty pig is another.

20
00:03:55,630 --> 00:03:59,327
There's no difference!
This is unfair and unjust.

21
00:04:00,835 --> 00:04:02,496
How could you be so heartless?

22
00:04:02,604 --> 00:04:04,868
Come here.
I want to show you something.

23
00:04:04,973 --> 00:04:07,134
You see that? You see?

24
00:04:07,909 --> 00:04:10,537
There's 11 pigs and only 10 teats.

25
00:04:10,979 --> 00:04:12,674
Sow can't feed it, honey.

26
00:04:14,149 --> 00:04:15,514
Then I will.

27
00:04:22,724 --> 00:04:26,387
I'll feed you and take care of you and...

28
00:04:29,531 --> 00:04:31,931
...absolutely will not let you kill him.

29
00:04:47,249 --> 00:04:51,117
- Hey! When did Fern get a pig?
- Avery, it's rude to point. Give me that.

30
00:04:51,219 --> 00:04:54,484
Come, sit, eat your breakfast.
The bus will be here any minute.

31
00:04:55,090 --> 00:04:56,284
Good morning.

32
00:04:56,825 --> 00:04:58,656
Hey, Pop, can I have a pig, too?

33
00:04:58,760 --> 00:05:01,228
No. I only give pigs to early risers.

34
00:05:01,730 --> 00:05:04,824
Fern was up before dawn,
ridding the world of injustice.

35
00:05:06,935 --> 00:05:09,563
Fern, put that pig down
and get to school.

36
00:05:09,671 --> 00:05:10,797
Avery.

37
00:05:11,640 --> 00:05:13,005
- See ya.
- Bye, Pop.

38
00:05:13,208 --> 00:05:14,800
Have a good one, buddy.

39
00:05:16,845 --> 00:05:19,439
Says here we're gonna get
a lot of rain this month.

40
00:05:25,854 --> 00:05:28,015
Fern! Your books!

41
00:05:31,660 --> 00:05:32,649
Bye.

42
00:05:33,061 --> 00:05:35,689
Class, these are some of the questions

43
00:05:35,797 --> 00:05:40,131
that you're likely to be asked
in the exam this week.

44
00:05:40,669 --> 00:05:44,867
So, please take particular note
of every one.

45
00:05:47,976 --> 00:05:51,139
You got to be quiet, okay?
You're gonna get me in trouble.

46
00:05:51,246 --> 00:05:52,645
Drink that.

47
00:05:55,250 --> 00:05:58,777
So, it's just a matter of
following these questions

48
00:05:58,887 --> 00:06:00,855
and learning the answers.

49
00:06:04,726 --> 00:06:06,284
Fern, what's going on?

50
00:06:06,761 --> 00:06:07,955
Nothing.

51
00:06:09,998 --> 00:06:11,761
Fern, what's in your desk?

52
00:06:12,901 --> 00:06:14,562
- Nothing.
- Open it.

53
00:06:29,284 --> 00:06:30,876
Thank you, Mrs. Arable.

54
00:06:31,619 --> 00:06:34,144
Fern, you know better.

55
00:06:34,255 --> 00:06:38,157
It's a pig, okay?
It's not a toy, not a doll, not a baby.

56
00:06:38,259 --> 00:06:39,453
A pig.

57
00:06:39,894 --> 00:06:42,419
And you need to start
treating it like one.

58
00:06:50,038 --> 00:06:51,596
This is going too far.

59
00:06:59,047 --> 00:07:01,413
I know she loves animals,
but you have to tell her.

60
00:07:01,516 --> 00:07:04,212
- I know. She's just so happy with it.
- I know.

61
00:07:13,461 --> 00:07:14,951
Doesrt that feel good?

62
00:07:15,063 --> 00:07:18,191
Fern, I'm really sorry, honey,
but it's been long enough.

63
00:07:18,500 --> 00:07:19,592
What?

64
00:07:19,701 --> 00:07:21,396
Look, he's not a baby anymore.

65
00:07:21,503 --> 00:07:24,734
I can't have you keeping what will soon
be a 300-pound pet around the house.

66
00:07:24,839 --> 00:07:25,897
No.

67
00:07:26,541 --> 00:07:29,908
Can't he stay in the barn? Please, Dad?

68
00:07:30,545 --> 00:07:31,842
- No.
- Please?

69
00:07:31,980 --> 00:07:34,005
No. Fern, look.
You know I've been selling the animals

70
00:07:34,115 --> 00:07:36,276
to get the new harvesting equipment.

71
00:07:36,584 --> 00:07:39,610
Pretty soon there's gonna be
no place in the barn for a pig.

72
00:07:40,288 --> 00:07:42,153
I promised I'd take care of him.

73
00:07:42,257 --> 00:07:44,691
Well, I'm letting you
out of your promise.

74
00:07:44,859 --> 00:07:47,987
I didn't promise you. I promised Wilbur.

75
00:07:49,230 --> 00:07:50,697
What about Homer?

76
00:07:51,433 --> 00:07:52,900
He has animals.

77
00:07:53,735 --> 00:07:55,032
Uncle Homer?

78
00:07:56,137 --> 00:07:58,537
I'm sure he could make room for a pig.

79
00:08:04,579 --> 00:08:05,603
Yeah.

80
00:08:05,914 --> 00:08:07,814
He'd be right across the road.

81
00:08:21,362 --> 00:08:26,322
Go to sleep, my little one

82
00:08:26,901 --> 00:08:32,066
The sun has said goodbye for now

83
00:08:32,807 --> 00:08:38,040
The moon shines on your beautiful face

84
00:08:41,349 --> 00:08:44,409
My mom used to sing that to me
to make me feel safe.

85
00:08:45,920 --> 00:08:47,114
Good night,

86
00:08:49,657 --> 00:08:50,954
Wilbur.

87
00:08:59,234 --> 00:09:03,568
Fern had walked across the road to her
uncle's barn hundreds of times before,

88
00:09:04,105 --> 00:09:06,630
but it had never felt so far away.

89
00:09:07,242 --> 00:09:10,109
It was just a big red barn
full of typical stuff.

90
00:09:14,849 --> 00:09:18,148
Come to think of it,
it couldn't have been more ordinary.

91
00:09:19,153 --> 00:09:21,713
But sometimes,
when you take two ordinary things

92
00:09:21,823 --> 00:09:24,314
and put them together
at just the right time,

93
00:09:24,659 --> 00:09:27,753
there's a chance they'll become
two less ordinary things.

94
00:09:29,197 --> 00:09:32,997
That runty pig, for instance,
and that big old smelly barn.

95
00:09:33,735 --> 00:09:37,068
One sniff, and you knew it was a place
full of living things.

96
00:09:38,039 --> 00:09:40,974
But that didn't necessarily mean
it was full of life.

97
00:09:41,075 --> 00:09:42,474
It's okay. It's okay.

98
00:09:42,577 --> 00:09:45,171
Nope. For that, this barn needed a pig.

99
00:09:45,280 --> 00:09:46,645
This isn't so bad.

100
00:09:47,549 --> 00:09:49,073
Only no one knew it yet.

101
00:09:49,183 --> 00:09:50,514
Don't be afraid.

102
00:09:55,890 --> 00:09:57,152
You'll be okay.

103
00:10:02,397 --> 00:10:04,194
I'll come see you every day.

104
00:10:04,666 --> 00:10:07,157
I'll be around so much
you'll be sick of me.

105
00:10:14,309 --> 00:10:15,606
I love you.

106
00:10:28,089 --> 00:10:29,989
Avery, the bus is here!

107
00:10:32,727 --> 00:10:35,389
- Did you remember your sister's lunch?
- Got it!

108
00:11:02,757 --> 00:11:03,781
What the hay?

109
00:11:03,891 --> 00:11:06,689
- What's he doing?
- Probably-obably something smart.

110
00:11:06,794 --> 00:11:09,285
- Pigs are smart.
- Pigs are not smart!

111
00:11:09,397 --> 00:11:12,059
Apparently, they're as intelligent
as dolphins.

112
00:11:12,900 --> 00:11:14,663
Advantage dolphin.

113
00:11:14,769 --> 00:11:17,397
- He's going to knock himself out.
- Yeah! That's using your head!

114
00:11:17,505 --> 00:11:19,837
How many times is he going to try that?

115
00:11:21,676 --> 00:11:23,837
- Pig's out!
- I told you pigs are smart.

116
00:11:23,945 --> 00:11:25,810
That's going to leave a mark.

117
00:11:26,881 --> 00:11:29,850
- Oh, look, Bits. Pig's out.
- Sure is out.

118
00:11:29,951 --> 00:11:31,145
Out of his mind!

119
00:11:35,890 --> 00:11:37,858
Homer!

120
00:11:38,826 --> 00:11:40,054
Lurvy!

121
00:11:40,728 --> 00:11:42,593
- Pig's out!
- Pig's out, pig's out, pig's out!

122
00:11:42,697 --> 00:11:45,632
- How about you walk a little faster?
- Wait your turn!

123
00:11:45,767 --> 00:11:48,463
Wait! Wait! Fern, come back!

124
00:11:49,604 --> 00:11:50,798
Just run!

125
00:11:50,905 --> 00:11:54,397
Run, pig! Be free! I would if I could.

126
00:11:54,509 --> 00:11:55,533
Retreat!

127
00:11:55,643 --> 00:11:57,907
- Retreat!
- Don't retreat, pig! Giddyup!

128
00:11:58,012 --> 00:12:00,810
- Oh, no! Not the smokehouse!
- No! Not the smokehouse!

129
00:12:04,886 --> 00:12:07,081
- Is he looking?
- Yeah, he's seen it.

130
00:12:07,188 --> 00:12:08,917
- Think he knows what it is?
- Of course not.

131
00:12:09,023 --> 00:12:11,651
He's a spring pig.
He doesn't know anything.

132
00:12:13,561 --> 00:12:16,462
Here, pig, pig, pig!

133
00:12:18,800 --> 00:12:21,769
Don't fall for it. You're out.

134
00:12:22,603 --> 00:12:24,195
And you're back in.

135
00:12:24,305 --> 00:12:25,932
Here you go, piggy.

136
00:12:26,808 --> 00:12:28,571
Attaboy. Eat it up.

137
00:12:28,676 --> 00:12:32,772
Sold out for slop.
I'd have been to the county line by now.

138
00:12:32,880 --> 00:12:34,905
He'd have made it
if you'd have just let me talk.

139
00:12:35,016 --> 00:12:37,484
- Made it to where? He's a pig!
- He's a pig.

140
00:12:37,985 --> 00:12:42,012
Sorry I made such a fuss.
Your suggestions were really good,

141
00:12:42,123 --> 00:12:45,854
but I think I'd better stay here.
Ferrs going to be back soon, anyway.

142
00:12:45,960 --> 00:12:48,451
He's just stupid as a stick, poor thing.

143
00:12:48,563 --> 00:12:50,656
- Should we speak to him?
- Certainly not!

144
00:12:50,765 --> 00:12:51,789
Certainly not.

145
00:12:51,899 --> 00:12:54,595
Sweetheart, it sounded-ounded
almost like you said

146
00:12:54,702 --> 00:12:56,533
you'd run and be free if you could.

147
00:12:56,637 --> 00:12:59,162
I meant if I were a pig.

148
00:12:59,273 --> 00:13:01,400
You know what happens to pigs
around here.

149
00:13:01,509 --> 00:13:04,808
Yes, I do.
And it should never, ever be spoken of.

150
00:13:16,390 --> 00:13:18,187
I'm gonna miss you today.

151
00:13:18,593 --> 00:13:20,493
See you when I get back, okay?

152
00:13:23,164 --> 00:13:25,962
All right, I gotta go, okay? See you later.

153
00:13:33,775 --> 00:13:34,742
Bye.

154
00:13:50,725 --> 00:13:53,193
Goodbye, Fern. Hurry back.

155
00:13:57,698 --> 00:13:59,165
Hi.

156
00:13:59,267 --> 00:14:00,632
My name's Wilbur.

157
00:14:01,335 --> 00:14:02,962
Anyone want to play?

158
00:14:03,704 --> 00:14:04,932
Anyone?

159
00:14:06,073 --> 00:14:09,366
It's raining, you know.
And you know what you get with rain?

160
00:14:09,777 --> 00:14:11,074
- Lightning.
- Typhoons.

161
00:14:11,179 --> 00:14:12,476
- Cholera.
- Dysentery.

162
00:14:12,580 --> 00:14:14,207
- Frizzy hair.
- That sad feeling.

163
00:14:14,315 --> 00:14:15,612
No, mud!

164
00:14:15,716 --> 00:14:17,775
What the heck is he doing now?

165
00:14:18,319 --> 00:14:20,480
Hey, come on. You wanna join me?
Come on! Let's go!

166
00:14:20,588 --> 00:14:22,146
Let's go, let's go, let's go!

167
00:14:22,256 --> 00:14:25,384
Let's not.
How many times must I tell you?

168
00:14:25,493 --> 00:14:29,259
Just because we're sheep,
it doesn't mean we have to follow.

169
00:14:29,530 --> 00:14:31,122
Think for yourselves.

170
00:14:31,232 --> 00:14:32,199
- Yourselves. Quite right!
- Look at me!

171
00:14:32,300 --> 00:14:34,564
- No, no, no. Yourselves.
- Myself?

172
00:14:36,337 --> 00:14:39,465
Hey, kid, this is a barn.
We don't play, we work.

173
00:14:39,574 --> 00:14:41,542
- Some of us, anyway.
- "Some of us"?

174
00:14:41,642 --> 00:14:44,611
Are you implying, lke,
that we don't work?

175
00:14:44,712 --> 00:14:48,341
Because we work bloody hard,
thank you!

176
00:14:48,449 --> 00:14:50,508
Hard? You grow hair!

177
00:14:51,886 --> 00:14:53,683
"Grow hair." Good one!

178
00:14:53,955 --> 00:14:55,445
Excuse me.

179
00:14:55,556 --> 00:14:59,492
And is that your contribution to society,
you gassy rib eyes?

180
00:14:59,594 --> 00:15:01,084
Filthy hairball!

181
00:15:01,195 --> 00:15:03,356
- Rib eyes!
- Dirty lintball!

182
00:15:03,464 --> 00:15:04,522
Zip it.

183
00:15:04,632 --> 00:15:05,724
- They're at it again.
- Rib eyes! Rib eyes!

184
00:15:05,833 --> 00:15:08,529
It's really slippery. That's the fun part!

185
00:15:08,636 --> 00:15:11,503
Little itty-bitty pig,
could you come here, please?

186
00:15:13,274 --> 00:15:15,333
You said your name is Wilbur, right?

187
00:15:15,443 --> 00:15:17,206
That's right. What's your name?

188
00:15:17,311 --> 00:15:18,835
- Gussy.
- Gussy?

189
00:15:18,946 --> 00:15:21,176
- Great name!
- Thank you, Wilbur.

190
00:15:21,282 --> 00:15:24,911
Now, you're so cute and pink,
but you're wasting your time.

191
00:15:25,019 --> 00:15:26,247
These animals won't play.

192
00:15:26,354 --> 00:15:28,015
- What about you?
- Me?

193
00:15:28,122 --> 00:15:30,590
Well, I have to stay on my eggs.

194
00:15:30,725 --> 00:15:32,784
Oh, wow! Look at that!

195
00:15:33,094 --> 00:15:35,460
Otherwise, of course, I'd love to play.

196
00:15:35,563 --> 00:15:37,497
So, why can't you play?

197
00:15:37,598 --> 00:15:41,193
Because what's good for the goose
is good for the gander.

198
00:15:41,302 --> 00:15:43,998
What about the rest of you?
Don't any of you like to play?

199
00:15:44,105 --> 00:15:46,073
Can't play on three empty stomachs.

200
00:15:46,173 --> 00:15:50,735
Well, for us there's this whole
smell-of-wet-wool business. Ghastly!

201
00:15:50,845 --> 00:15:54,042
See? I'm afraid
it's just not a play kind of place.

202
00:15:54,248 --> 00:15:55,806
But you're all friends, right?

203
00:15:55,917 --> 00:15:58,442
Sure. We've been here together
our whole lives.

204
00:15:58,552 --> 00:16:02,716
I'm not so sure being in the same place
is the same as being friends.

205
00:16:07,895 --> 00:16:10,887
I'm not hungry.
I just wanted someone to play with me.

206
00:16:12,333 --> 00:16:13,630
What's that?

207
00:16:14,302 --> 00:16:15,599
What is...

208
00:16:18,105 --> 00:16:19,265
Could it be?

209
00:16:20,942 --> 00:16:22,307
Slops!

210
00:16:22,410 --> 00:16:26,676
Oh, joy. It seems the pig slop
has brought out the rodent.

211
00:16:26,781 --> 00:16:28,772
Moldy cheese. Oh, yeah.

212
00:16:31,752 --> 00:16:34,312
Did I have salami last night?

213
00:16:36,424 --> 00:16:38,415
Yep. I guess I did.

214
00:16:38,526 --> 00:16:41,256
- Oh, charming.
- Disgusting creature!

215
00:16:41,362 --> 00:16:42,659
Hi, there.

216
00:16:44,198 --> 00:16:45,597
Oh, you're a pig.

217
00:16:47,001 --> 00:16:48,628
You're a pig.

218
00:16:49,070 --> 00:16:50,628
Pig equals slop.

219
00:16:52,506 --> 00:16:54,633
The rat is happy.

220
00:16:54,875 --> 00:16:56,103
My name's Wilbur.

221
00:16:56,210 --> 00:16:58,906
Do you have a name?
Or is it just "the rat"?

222
00:17:04,085 --> 00:17:06,212
Did you say "just the rat"?

223
00:17:06,988 --> 00:17:10,287
For your information, pig, the rat rules.

224
00:17:10,391 --> 00:17:14,487
We were here long before your kind,
and we'll be here long after.

225
00:17:14,595 --> 00:17:16,153
So, you just keep that in mind

226
00:17:16,263 --> 00:17:19,596
next time you feel like
reducing me to "just the rat."

227
00:17:19,700 --> 00:17:21,497
You called yourself "the rat."

228
00:17:21,769 --> 00:17:24,602
I can call me that. You can't.

229
00:17:25,106 --> 00:17:27,074
So you don't have a name?

230
00:17:28,442 --> 00:17:30,910
Of course I do. It's Templeton.

231
00:17:31,178 --> 00:17:33,043
Templeton? Great name!

232
00:17:33,147 --> 00:17:36,344
- Oh, gee, thanks.
- Hey! You want to play, Templeton?

233
00:17:36,450 --> 00:17:39,817
For so many reasons, no.

234
00:17:40,721 --> 00:17:42,780
See, I don't play.

235
00:17:43,024 --> 00:17:46,824
I gnaw, I spy, I eat, I hide.
Me in a nutshell.

236
00:17:46,927 --> 00:17:48,758
Couldrt you just stay and chat?

237
00:17:48,863 --> 00:17:50,831
Chat? Let me see.

238
00:17:51,098 --> 00:17:54,226
Gnaw, spy, eat, hide.

239
00:17:54,335 --> 00:17:56,735
Nope, "chat" ain't on the list.

240
00:18:04,345 --> 00:18:06,313
The rat is handsome.

241
00:18:33,340 --> 00:18:36,309
Tonight I dream of slop!

242
00:18:40,247 --> 00:18:44,013
Fern, you are not going to see
that pig again. It's too late.

243
00:18:44,118 --> 00:18:45,676
But he's expecting me!

244
00:18:45,853 --> 00:18:49,118
And I'm expecting you to finish
your homework and go straight to bed.

245
00:18:49,223 --> 00:18:51,748
But, Mom, I always tell him good night!

246
00:18:51,859 --> 00:18:54,623
- Not tonight.
- He can't sleep if I don't.

247
00:18:57,565 --> 00:18:58,793
Good night.

248
00:18:59,600 --> 00:19:00,862
Good night.

249
00:19:02,536 --> 00:19:03,696
Good night!

250
00:19:03,804 --> 00:19:05,101
Good night.

251
00:19:05,940 --> 00:19:07,805
