last night.

282
00:20:54,014 --> 00:20:55,845
I suppose that would be me.

283
00:20:56,417 --> 00:20:57,441
Okay.

284
00:20:57,551 --> 00:20:59,644
- I can't see you.
- Up here, in the corner.

285
00:21:01,888 --> 00:21:03,355
The other corner.

286
00:21:04,724 --> 00:21:07,693
I'm sorry. I still can't see you.

287
00:21:07,961 --> 00:21:10,191
Move a little closer. I'll come down.

288
00:21:23,810 --> 00:21:25,971
Hi. You're a...

289
00:21:26,079 --> 00:21:28,411
Look, I've got a long day ahead of me
and I'm trying to get a little...

290
00:21:28,515 --> 00:21:30,278
Spider! Spider! Get it away from me!

291
00:21:30,383 --> 00:21:32,681
Get it away! Get it away!

292
00:21:33,353 --> 00:21:34,877
All right, keep your distance there.

293
00:21:34,988 --> 00:21:38,822
- That thing is creepy.
- Golly! You're not being rude, are you?

294
00:21:38,925 --> 00:21:43,157
No, no, no. I meant "creepy"
in a nice way. You know, creepy good.

295
00:21:43,263 --> 00:21:44,355
Disgusting!

296
00:21:44,497 --> 00:21:46,727
- They eat their menfolk, you know.
- I know!

297
00:21:46,833 --> 00:21:50,030
Well? Still want to chat,
or are you gonna join them?

298
00:21:50,136 --> 00:21:52,400
I've never met a spider before.

299
00:21:53,339 --> 00:21:55,136
Did you make that?

300
00:21:55,341 --> 00:21:57,741
Is that what you were concentrating on
last night?

301
00:21:57,844 --> 00:22:00,472
- Yes.
- It's amazing.

302
00:22:01,347 --> 00:22:03,872
Think you could teach me
how to make one of those?

303
00:22:07,687 --> 00:22:09,382
Hold that thought, please.

304
00:22:12,325 --> 00:22:14,555
- What are you doing?
- Making breakfast.

305
00:22:14,828 --> 00:22:16,557
- Oh, boy.
- Relax.

306
00:22:16,830 --> 00:22:20,163
First, I give him a little nip
to anesthetize him,

307
00:22:20,266 --> 00:22:21,824
so he'll be more comfortable.

308
00:22:21,935 --> 00:22:23,698
It's a little service I throw in.

309
00:22:23,803 --> 00:22:25,532
Then I wrap him up.

310
00:22:25,772 --> 00:22:29,731
Then I just say grace because,
well, that's always nice,

311
00:22:29,843 --> 00:22:31,401
and he'll make a
perfectly delicious meal.

312
00:22:31,511 --> 00:22:34,275
So, you eat flies?

313
00:22:34,547 --> 00:22:36,071
No, no, no.

314
00:22:37,217 --> 00:22:38,684
